📘 Subject: General Studies Paper I (Prelims – Polity)
🧠 Topic: Constituent Assembly & Making of the Indian Constitution

(Continuation of Indian Polity after historical background.)

1️⃣ Core Teaching (Simple, Exam-Oriented)
🔹 Formation of the Constituent Assembly

The Constituent Assembly was formed in 1946 to draft the Constitution of India.

Basis:

Cabinet Mission Plan (1946)

Total Members:

Originally 389 members

After partition:

Reduced to 299 members

🔵 Election of Members

Members were indirectly elected by:

Provincial Legislative Assemblies

Seats distribution:

Provinces

Princely States

🔹 Important Leaders
Position	Person
President	Dr. Rajendra Prasad
Drafting Committee Chairman	Dr. B.R. Ambedkar
Vice President	H.C. Mukherjee
Constitutional Advisor	B.N. Rau
🔴 Drafting Committee (1947)

Headed by Dr. B.R. Ambedkar

Members included:

N. Gopalaswami Ayyangar

Alladi Krishnaswami Ayyar

K.M. Munshi

Mohammad Saadullah

📌 Known as Architect of Indian Constitution

🔹 Time Taken

First meeting: 9 December 1946

Constitution adopted: 26 November 1949

Total time taken:
👉 2 years, 11 months, 18 days

🔹 Important Committees
Committee	Chairman
Union Powers Committee	Jawaharlal Nehru
Provincial Constitution Committee	Sardar Patel
Drafting Committee	B.R. Ambedkar
Fundamental Rights Committee	J.B. Kripalani
🔹 Key Features of the Drafting Process

Open debates

Public participation

Amendments discussed

Influences from many constitutions

